<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-28T17:56:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-28T17:56:00-05:00" n="769" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d769">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">816.48/75: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Arnold</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-28T17:00:00-05:56"><hi rend="italic">April 28,
                                        1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                    April 29, 12.30 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Martial law declared today. Damage much greater than first anticipated.
                            Number of deaths at present reported 40 persons. Notify Weinberg’s
                            parents Washington he is safe.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Arnold</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>